  "prompt": "Can Windex leach through aquarium glass?",
  "response": "Windex and similar glass cleaners are not recommended for use on aquarium glass. The chemicals in these products, such as ammonia and alcohol, can indeed leach through the glass and into the water, which can be harmful to fish and other aquatic life. Even if you thoroughly rinse the glass, there's still a risk of residue affecting the water quality.\n\nFor cleaning aquarium glass, it's safer to use a specialized aquarium-safe cleaner or simply a soft cloth or algae scraper designed for aquariums. These methods help maintain a healthy environment for your aquatic pets.",
